This paper deals with natural language processing and social intuition, which are common themes in the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the analysis of human experiences and social interactions, which could fall under the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SI) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
